         <abstract>
            <p>Numerically stable algorithms are given for updating the Gram-Schmidt QR factorization of an $m \times n$ matrix $A (m \geqslant n)$ when $A$ is modified by a matrix of rank one, or when a row or column is inserted or deleted. The algorithms require $O(mn)$ operations per update, and are based on the use of elementary two-by-two reflection matrices and the Gram-Schmidt process with reorthogonalization. An error analysis of the reorthogonalization process provides rigorous justification for the correpsonding ALGOL procedures.</p>
          </abstract>
